name: ipc.server.purge.interval
description:
Define how often calls are cleaned up in the server.
    The default is 15 minutes. The unit is minutes.

name: dfs.namenode.redundancy.interval.seconds
description:
The periodicity in seconds with which the namenode computes 
  low redundancy work for datanodes. Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive),
  as described in dfs.heartbeat.interval.

name: fs.df.interval
description: Disk usage statistics refresh interval in msec.

name: mapreduce.task.io.sort.mb
description:
The total amount of buffer memory to use while sorting
  files, in megabytes.  By default, gives each merge stream 1MB, which
  should minimize seeks.

name: dfs.webhdfs.netty.high.watermark
description: High watermark configuration to Netty for Datanode WebHdfs.

name: mapreduce.shuffle.pathcache.expire-after-access-minutes
description:
The length of time after an entry is last accessed that it
    should be automatically removed.

name: mapreduce.job.end-notification.retry.attempts
description:
The number of times the submitter of the job wants to retry job
    end notification if it fails. This is capped by
    mapreduce.job.end-notification.max.attempts
